summary: The document is a classified release under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992, detailing information related to the JFK assassination system. It features an identification form concerning a Cuban exile leader and involves multiple agencies including the FBI and CIA. The document, marked as Secret, was last reviewed in 1998 and received approval in 2015.
key_findings: Released under the JFK Assassination Records Act of 1992.
Details a Cuban exile leader and references the Cuban Embassy in Mexico City.
Originated from the CIA and directed to the FBI Director.
Classified as Secret, with a last review in 1998 and approval in 2015.
